    Cluster stability across resolutions

    VisClusterStability.Rd

    Assess clustering stability by resampling cells and varying resolution.

    Usage

    VisClusterStability(
  object,
  resolution_range = seq(0.2, 1.2, by = 0.2),
  dims = 1:10,
  reps = 5,
  prop = 0.8,
  palette = "C"
)

    Arguments

    object

    A Seurat object with PCA computed.

    resolution_range

    Numeric vector of resolutions, e.g., seq(0.2, 1.2, by=0.2).

    dims

    PCA dimensions to use.

    reps

    Number of resampling repetitions.

    prop

    Proportion of cells to sample per repetition.

    palette

    Viridis palette option.

    Value

    A list with summary data.frame and a ggplot summarizing stability.

    Examples

    obj <- SeuratVisProExample()
